success.question_text: What is the ratio of 8 cm to 20 mm in simplest form?
success.question_hint:
• Rewrite 8 cm in millimetres.
  • Express as a ratio and then simplify.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A ratio involves two or more quantities that, when simplified, must be expressed with the same units. For example, the ratio of 8 cm to 20 mm is not 8:20.

success.question_hint:
• Enter 15% into your calculator as a decimal or fraction.
  • Considering each answer in the options, you need to change 3 tonnes into kilograms.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

An easy way to find 15% of an amount is to first find 10% (by dividing the amount by 10), then to find 5% (by halving 10%) and add the two results.

success.question_hint:
• For each of the options, multiply and then express your answers in hours and minutes.
  • You need to choose the smallest amount of time.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Be very careful if using a calculator to work out times. Remember that time is not a decimal.

success.question_text: How many square metres are there in one square kilometre?
success.question_hint:
• Imagine two identical squares: one has a side of 1 km and the other 1000 metres.
  • Find the area of both squares.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Where possible, work in the units of the required answer when finding areas or volumes. It is always easier to convert single units than to convert square or cubic units.

success.question_text: What is the volume of the box? Type the number, not the unit of measurement, in the box, e.g. for 2 cm3 type only 2.
success.question_hint:
• Imagine the net forming a rectangular prism.
  • The volume formula is V = lbh.

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows the net of a box:

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The volume of any prism can be found by multiplying the area of the cross-section by the perpendicular height.

success.question_hint:
• The area of a triangle is found using the formula Area equals half the base times the height.
  • You need to use the perpendicular height.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The height used when finding the area of a triangle must be the perpendicular height. It must be at right angles to the base.

success.question_hint:
• Change 3.55 litres to millilitres before adding.
  • After finding the total, you need to convert back to litres.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Change measurements into the same units before adding or subtracting.

success.question_text: At the same speed, how many laps will the car have completed in an hour?
success.question_hint:
• Work out how many seconds are in one hour.
  • Divide this answer by the time it takes to complete one lap.

stimulus_2.text: A racing car can complete a lap of a race circuit in 80 seconds.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Make sure you can convert seconds to minutes and hours and vice versa.

success.question_text: What is the length of the radius of the circle?
success.question_hint:
• The circumference of a circle can be found using the formula Circumference equals pi times the diameter.
  • After finding the diameter you can halve it to find the radius.

stimulus_1.text: The circumference of a circle is 37.7 cm.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The diameter of a circle is the distance across the circle through the centre. The radius is half the diameter.

success.question_text:
If the sides of the square are 2 cm, what is the volume of the remaining solid?

Type the number, not the unit of measurement, in the box, e.g. for 2 cm3 type only 2.
success.question_hint:
• Find the volume of the large cube and the volume of the small cut-out cube.
  • Subtract to find the volume of the remaining solid.

stimulus_1.text: A wooden cube has sides of length 6 cm. A ‘square hole’ is cut through the cube:

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The volume of any prism is found by multiplying the area of the cross-section by the perpendicular height.

success.question_hint:
• The triangle will have a right angle only if the three side lengths form a Pythagorean triad.
  • This means the square of the longest side equals the sum of the squares of the other two sides.

stimulus_1.text: Which triangle, when accurately drawn to scale, will contain a right angle?

review_5.column_1_text:
Tip

If the square on the longest side of a triangle is equal to the sum of the squares on the other two sides, then the triangle must be right-angled.

success.question_text:
How many metres long is each side of the square?

Type the number of metres in the box below without the m sign, e.g. 43 for 43 m.
success.question_hint:
• The area of a square is the square of the length of a side.
  • This means the side length will be the square root of the area.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

There are always two values whose square is equal to a particular number, one positive and one negative. But in practical situations the negative value cannot apply. For example, in this question the length of a side must be positive.

success.question_text:
What is the perimeter of the remaining shape?

Type the number, not the unit of measurement, in the box, e.g. for 2 cm type only 2.
success.question_hint:
• The cut out means the perimeter of the new shape is longer than the original.
  • Find the perimeter of the original square and add the small lengths that have been included.

stimulus_1.text: A square of side length 3 cm was cut from one side of a square of side length 12 cm as shown in the diagram:

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

It is not necessary to know all the individual measurements to find the perimeter of a shape. As long as you know the total length of each of the sides, the perimeter can be found.

success.question_text: What is the surface area of this prism?
success.question_hint:
• There are two triangular faces and three rectangular faces on the triangular prism.
  • The area of the triangular faces is found using the formula Area equals half the base times the height.

review_5.column_1_text:
Tip

The surface area of any prism is the total area of all the faces.

success.question_text: Which is the best estimate of the amount of fuel, in litres, used by the car on the journey?
success.question_hint:
• Work out the travel time, and, with the average speed, find the distance between the two places.
  • Find the number of 100 kms in the distance and multiply this answer by 9 L.

stimulus_2.text: A car left Smithtown at 9:35 am and arrived at Greensburg at 1:05 pm on the same day. The average speed of the car was 74 km/h and it used fuel at the rate of 9L/100 km.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

If a question asks for the best estimate you can still find the exact answer if you want and if it is easy to do.

success.question_text:
What is the volume of the cube?

Type the number, not the unit of measurement, in the box, e.g. for 2 cm3 type only 2.
success.question_hint:
• Use the formula A = 6s2 to find the length of each side of the cube.
  • Use this answer to find the volume using the formula V = s3.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The surface area of any prism is the total area of all the faces. The volume of any prism is found by multiplying the area of the cross-section by the perpendicular height.
